Vehmic courts in Germany consisted of secret meetings of "free judges" loyal only to the Emperor who administered justice to unpunished criminals and left them on trees afterwards. Wonder if the similarity is intentional or it's all just a natural phenomenon that springs up.
They also used to swear oaths on skulls. Has to do with this Bushido mindset of always seeing your death in front of your eyes and living like you are already dead. Old custom.
